Open it with cmd+shift+e

What it currently does:

* Track filesystem changes with FSEvents.
* Toggle hidden file visibility.
* Create new files and folders.
* Rename files and folders.
* Double click a folder to change the project work-directory.
* Open a file in the current or a new tab, depending on your normal settings, with alt+click.
* Open files in split views.
* Open files with external apps.
* Browse with the j and k keys.
